name: QINLOCK
indications: qinlock indicated treatment adult patients advanced gastrointestinal stromal tumor ( gist ) received prior treatment 3 kinase inhibitors , including imatinib .
contraindications: recommended : 150 mg orally daily without food . ( 2.1 )
warningsAndPrecautions: qinlock 50 mg tablets white off-white , oval shaped , debossed “ dc1 ” one side . 90-count bottles ndc 73207-101-30 dispense original container . store original container desiccant protect moisture light . replace cap securely time opening . discard desiccant . store 20°c 25°c ( 68°f 77°f ) ; excursion permitted 15°c 30°c ( 59°f 86°f ) [ usp controlled room temperature ] .
indications_original: QINLOCK is indicated for the treatment of adult patients with advanced gastrointestinal stromal tumor (GIST) who have received prior treatment with 3 or more kinase inhibitors, including imatinib.
contraindications_original: Recommended Dosage : 150 mg orally once daily with or without food. ( 2.1 )
warningsAndPrecautions_original:
QINLOCK 50 mg tablets are white to off-white, oval shaped, and debossed with “DC1” on one side.

                  
                     
                        90-count bottles            NDC 73207-101-30

                  
                  Dispense in original container only. Store in the original container with the desiccant to protect from moisture and light. Replace cap securely each time after opening. Do not discard desiccant.

                  Store at 20°C to 25°C (68°F to 77°F); excursion permitted between 15°C to 30°C (59°F to 86°F) [see USP Controlled Room Temperature].
